column14: **** UPDATED 2023-06-26. Wrong equation used for price meter. Updated equation can be found in attached FV2. Correct equation added 1.2cms - LKR*** **** UPDATED 2023-11-16. Adjusted the velocity angles on the mmnt from 0.98 to 0.94 based on the average angle that had been used in past high water measurements from 1989-2019. Corrected the final Q to 53.7 m3/s.   Conventional mmnt on d/s side of bridge 20m u/s of gauge + flowtracker mmnt of side channel that flows in between gauge and bridge. Conventional mmnt 55.5cms (Originally 54.3cms). Side channel flow tracker mmnt 0.5cms.  Used logger values since we did not trust our surveyed WL. Ran a consistent 0.98 angle adjustment for all panels during the conventional.  Piers on either end caused some deadzones. RB edge we called at pier and gave it a depth. LB edge had some flow around it so we accounted for this in our edge distance. Flowtracker mmnt was used as an estimate to account for missed flow during conventional, and did not follow WSC standards (e.g. panel Q>10%, <20 panels). @ Uncertainty: IVE method, 2-sigma value (IVE Value). @ HG appears to be tracking well. Surging up to 0.015 but reasonable given channel conditions.  Could not get a confident water level with +-0.05m surge and difficulty safely reaching orifice location. Did not apply SRC.  Mid-section
